uk.co.strangeskies.observable

Class ObservablePropertyImpl<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.strangeskies.observable.ObservablePropertyImpl<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of event message to produce
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observable<T>, ObservableProperty<T>, ObservableValue<T>, Property<T>

    public class ObservablePropertyImpl<T>
extends Object
implements ObservableProperty<T>
    A simple implementation of ObservableProperty which maintains a list of listeners to receive change events fired with set(Object).

    Addition and removal of observers, as well as the firing of events, are synchronized on the implementation object.
